data.title: Carpe and Diem: Seize the Friendship
data.description: Having met each other in middle school through gaming, Jaehyeok “Carpe” Lee and Min Sung “Diem” Bae have maintained a friendship from their path to pro and all the way into the Overwatch League. Danny Lim sits down with the two buddies before they face off against each other at the Atlanta Homestand

Babybay's Bastion: Atlanta Reign's Secret Weapon on Ilios
data.description: In this episode of Tactics, learn how the Atlanta Reign played around Babybay's Bastion on Ilios: Well to control the tempo of the game right from the start. It's all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: Getting hot in the South: Overwatch League heads to Atlanta
data.description: Things are heating up in Hot’lanta! When the Overwatch League takes over ATL, how will the away teams handle the heat? The competitors of the Atlanta Homestand discuss how they think the crowd will greet them.

data.title: The Dancing Outlaw – Jake and Mica learn to Dance
data.description: Overwatch League Insider Mica Burton takes Jake of the Houston Outlaws to get professional dance lessons. Will being agile in the Overwatch League translate to being agile on the dance floor?

data.title: My Hero: Winston
data.description: Paris Eternal's LHCloudy, London Spitfire's Gesture, Washington Justice's Janus, and Dallas Fuel's OGE share their insights on what makes Winston unique as a main tank! It's all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: OGE’s Redemption
data.description: Minseok “OGE” Son, the Dallas Fuel’s star tank sits down to discuss the struggles of replacing xQc in 2018, his 4-game suspension, and how the raw emotions of the Dallas Homestand affected him.

data.title: Painting the Town Pink with Guxue
data.description: Insider Emily Tang takes Hangzhou Spark Main Tank Qiulin “Guxue” Xu to paint the hero that made him famous and chat about the Spark’s upward trajectory.

data.title: Houston Outlaws: Back in the Saddle Again
data.description: Going winless in Stage 2 of the Overwatch League, the Houston Outlaws regathered over the All-Star break and came back swinging in Stage 3. Jake and Muma talk about the tough road ahead for the Outlaws and how they deal with the “haters”.

data.title: Saebyeolbe – Back in Blue
data.description: Being benched for the New York Excelsior for most of the 2019 season, star DPS player Jong-Ryeol “Saebyeolbe” Park didn’t know when he’d see playtime again. Grinding his way on Sombra, Saebyeolbe is back to prove he’s not done yet.
